121. The story ran that Idomeneus on his way home from Troy, being overtaken by a storin, vowed to sacrifice to Poseidon whatever first met him, if he reached Crete in safety. He was met by his son, whom he sacrificed in accordance with his vow. Crete was then visited by a plague, and the inhabitants expelled Idomeneus. Compare the story of Jephthah and his daughter, and the tale of Beauty and the Beast.
